content:
You can have multiple phone channels in your contact center for different purposes, such as Support and Sales. Each channel has its own phone number.

To route calls in a phone channel using an Omni-Channel flow, follow these steps:

From Setup, enter Voice and select Amazon Contact Centers or Partner Telephony Contact Centers.
Click the contact center and add a phone channel under Contact Center Channels.
Enter the channel properties:
	* Channel Name: The name of the phone channel
	* Phone Number: The phone number customers call to contact you on this channel
	* Routing Type: 
		+ Queue: Route calls to a specific queue
		+ Omni-Channel Flow: Dynamically route calls using an Omni-Channel flow and fallback queue (if the flow fails, the call is routed to the fallback queue)
		+ None: Do not specify a routing method (calls will fail if no instructions are provided)

Click Save.
title: Assigning Omni-Channel Flows to Phone Channels in Service Cloud
